<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-315-266  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 315 266.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  April 3 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>British Telecom unveils Concert.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   British Telecommunications PLC (services).andO;Topic:     TelecommunicationsConcert (Telephone service)Data CommunicationsMarketing StrategyUnited Kingdom.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BRITISH TELECOM UNVEILS CONCERT LONDON, ENGLAND, 1990 MAR 31 (NB) -- BritishTelecom (BT) has unveiled Concert, its most ambitious networking service todate.andP;  Using Concert, BT claims to be able to supply most companies' computerand data networking needs with the added bonus of conforming tointernationally agreed-upon standards.andM;Currently, any business, such as Newsbytes' UK bureau, must contract withseveral divisions of BT for the provision of various data network services(packet switching, private links, telex, etc.).andP;  Under Concert, businessescan have one contact office and phone number for the provision and support ofall of these services.andM;Announcing Concert in London last week, David Day, managing director of BT'scommunications systems division, said that the service takes BT several stepscloser towards its goal of becoming the world's most successfultelecommunications company.andM;&quot;Companies' networks have become the very lifeblood of their businesses.andO;Investment in such networks runs into millions of pounds.andP;  With worldwideliberalization, these networks are often patchworks of equipment from manydifferent suppliers,&quot; he said.andM;&quot;Concert is designed to cross the boundaries of public, private and hybridnetworks in both voice and data.andP;  Because networks are part of an overallinformation system, close cooperation with computer system suppliers isessential,&quot; he added.andM;Initially, Concert will draw together computer and data networking servicesunder one umbrella division with more than 1,000 systems architects,designers and software engineers.andP;  To support Concert, BT has established apurpose-built software centre in Glasgow.andM;(Steve Gold/19900331/Press Contact: BT Corporate Newsroom - Tel:071-356-5366; Public Contact: British Telecom - Tel: 071-726- 4444)</TEXT></DOC>